dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset contains GIS data for Nepal Local Units (Adm2). These new boundaries are officially recognized as part of the federal structure of Nepal.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: 2017 Local Unit boundaries (as polygons) of Nepal.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. District names converted from ALL CAPS to Proper Case. 2. Admin2 names "MadhyaNepal", "JayaPrithivi", "Chautara SangachokGadhi" and "SakhuwaPrasauni" were given a space separating names. 3. As instructed by IMO, ITOS has constructed p-codes using 2-letter ISO code "NL" in ITOS format. 4. Created and populated Admin0 name and p-code fields. 5. Created and populated District p-code field. Values come from the District p-code section of the Admin2 p-codes. 6. Fixed misspelled Admin2 name "Parsa Wildlife Resrve". 7. Admin2 spelling "Chitawan National Park" changed to "Chitwan National Park" for consistent spelling in the layer. 8. As instructed by IMO, the districts "Rukum" and "Nawalparasi" have been split in two. District name attribution in Admin2 has been changed to reflect this: Admin2 units in district "Rukum" with Admin1 "5" attribution have new district name "Rukum East". Admin2 units in district "Rukum" with Admin1 "6" attribution have new district name "Rukum West". Admin2 units in district "Nawalparasi" with Admin1 "5" attribution have new district name "Nawalparasi West". Admin2 units in district "Nawalparasi" with Admin1 "4" attribution have new district name "Nawalparasi East". 9. As instructed by IMO, ITOS has updated Admin2 names to match names in Excel sheet "npl_adminboundaries_tabulardata.v2.xlsx".
